cards.desc:
The objectives are clear but no measurable outcomes are described. 
The flexibility is also limited due to the lack of adequate mitigation strategies. 
Moreover the proposal fails to convince that the technology will be advantageous compared to the state of the art, thus limiting its impact.
The panel discussed the participation of the partner Mayo Clinic from the USA and decided that it is essential to the project because this partner brings spinal cord injury rehabilitation expertise unique to the consortium.
The panel advises the consortium not to resubmit the proposal without a substantial redrafting of the presentation of the research idea,
potentially including its revision.

email Victor his tasks on FetOpen

cards.desc:
Exploitation is not addressed in a good way, as the proposal mentions both IP protection for the
relevant parts of the project and a commercialization strategy, but the intention to patent some of the research outcomes is not accompanied by a clear description of what will be patented and how.
cards.name: 2 4 Measures to maximize

cards.desc:
The need to include partner from the third-country (USA) is not
sufficiently clearly described.
cards.name: 3 6  Consortium

cards.desc:
It is not clear why the milestone 2 (validated neuron) is in M42
and work package WP4 (neuron) ends in M34. There is a short interval between neuron deliverables and reflex arc deliverables posing a risk
if there will be enough time to use results from WP4 in WP5. Other deliverables, milestones and work packages are adequate.
Research methodology concentrates on in-vivo experiments, but lacks sufficient details about computer simulations and model verification
prior to in-vivo experiments. Management structure is acceptable. Allocation of resources is adequate. Risk analysis is provided, but proposed
measures are broadly described and general.
cards.name: 3 3 Implementation

cards.desc:
Some WP assignments are inconsistent with a partner's expertise, i.e. UEF as lead beneficiary for WP5 and responsible for D4.2 & D5.4 and SmartMe responsible for D4.3. There are important details missing in the description of T5.3, namely what sensory signals will be provided to the reflex arc and how the reflex arc will aid recovery of motor function. The protocol for training the rats following spinal cord injury or induced stroke is unclear, including how the reflex arc will be employed. It is not clear how different protocols will be compared to determine whether the reflex arc contributes to recovery. It is also not clear what is meant by "synthetic nucleus" (WP4). The management plan is short on details such as the composition of the international advisory board, its role and the logistics of communication and technology transfer among
partners.
cards.name: 3 2 Implementation

cards.desc:
However, the milestones are
limited in number and they come too late: the first at M12, the others at M42 and M48, respectively.This placement does not allow for a timely
intervention to put the activities on track whenever needed. Resource allocation is unbalanced towards one of the partners (MC). Risk
management is sufficiently addressed, although not very detailed, as only few risks are considered. The envisaged management structure is
good. The funding and the grant amount requested by MC, also compared with the grants of the other partners, is too high.
cards.name: 3 1 Implementation

cards.desc:
, but insufficiently addresses economic impact, social impact or impact on market creation.
Involvement of young researchers, SMEs and first-time participants is evident.
cards.name: 2 3 Expected impacts

cards.desc:
The scientific and technological impact of the outputs of the project will be mediocre. The memristive reflex arc, which is the one of the
principal outputs of the project, does not offer any clear advantages over conventional integrated circuit technology. The outcome of training
for recovery of function after spinal cord injury or induced stroke which is the other principal output is unlikely to be superior to current
alternative approaches.
cards.name: 2 2 Expected impacts

cards.desc:
The proposal addresses the main scientific and technological impact in a superficial way. For instance, the scientific contribution of the
proposal to the foundation of a new neuromorphic-prosthetic technology is claimed, but not sufficiently demonstrated comparing with existing trends. Moreover, there is a quite abstract provision for societal/economic innovation or market creation, but the concrete innovation elements and the real benefits are not elaborated with sufficient detail.
cards.name: 2 1 Expected impacts

cards.desc: Although it is plausible that an electrode interface between a memristive circuit and the spinal cord for the purpose of stimulation can be formed, the connection to the spinal cord will be sparse and non-specific.
cards.name: 1 9 High risk

cards.desc:
The research approach lacks flexibility since it is entirely dependent on the success of the memristive technology. There are no adequate mitigating strategies to salvage the project if the memristive approach fails. Although it is plausible that an electrode interface between a memristive circuit and the spinal cord for the purpose of stimulation can be formed, the
connection to the spinal cord will be sparse and non-specific. Hence it is not plausible that this approach will be beneficial for recovery of
impaired locomotion.
cards.name: 1 8th High risk

cards.desc: The performance of the targeted result will depend on the system size, but how the architecture can scale to a large number of neurons is not sufficiently discussed in the proposal. The claimed advantage of the proposed approach, i.e. that it does not require patients to carry the device on their body, against GPU-based technologies is not sufficiently credible, as one GPU can emulate millions of neurons, not just a few of them.
cards.name: 1 7 High risk

cards.desc:
Relevant state-of-the-art is not discussed sufficiently - the proposal mainly refers to the previous work of the researchers in the consortium.
While the previous work of the researchers is sufficient to allow plausibility of the proposed research, the proposal does not convincingly
position itself in the related work from other researchers.
cards.name: 1 4 Novelty

cards.desc:
The specific objective of the project of using a memristive reflex arc to
assist in recovery of function after spinal cord injury or stroke is not adequately described in terms of measurable outcomes. Given the
complexity of spinal cord circuits it is unrealistic to expect successful implementation of such a reflex arc within the duration of the project.
cards.name: 1 3 Vision

cards.desc: However, the proposal clearly states that the current approaches are radically different, but does not point at tangible, measurable performance indicators to be used for a comparison with them.

cards.desc:
Khasianov Airat, [26.05.17 00:26]
Уважаемый Айрат,

Для вовлечения академических разработок в инновационную деятельность Samsung Electronics
и в качестве платформы технологического сотрудничества в нашей компании с 2009 года действует ежегодная конкурсная программа Global Research Outreach (GRO):
http://www.sait.samsung.co.kr/saithome/Page.do?method=main&pagePath=01_about/&pageName=gro_overview

Программа открыта для участия университетов, а в случае России также институтов РАН.
Победившие участники конкурса получают финансирование до $100,000 на годовой проект, который может быть проделн до 3-х лет.

Тематики каждый год меняются, список актуальных тематик и их описание можно найти на сайте программы:
http://www.sait.samsung.co.kr/saithome/Page.do?method=main&pagePath=01_about/&pageName=ag_going

Помимо тематик указанных на сайте, рассматриваются также проекты по тематике Social Robot:
(1) Robot can learn and catch human's preference through real time interaction between human and robot.
    Robot can sustain interaction with human.
(2) Robot can express natural nonverbal behavior based on various emotion and context of interaction between human.
(3) Robot can synchronize nonverbal expression(pose, gesture, gaze, etc.) with speech (or verbal expression).
(4) Robot can understand human's emotions through multi modal recognition (visual, audio, text)

Крайний срок подачи заявок: 12 июня.
Объявление победителей – в августе.
Если вы заинтерсовались этой программой, и хотите поучаствовать в конкурсе по одной или нескольким тематикам,
мы будем рады проконсультировать вам по процедурным вовпросам.

Также мы подготовили небольшой guideline для потенциальных участников программы.

Best regards / С уважением,
